                           <p>Pedimental <objectType>sarcophagus lid</objectType> with akroteria, 
                              <dimensions><height unit="metre">0.39</height> <width unit="metre">2.05</width> <depth unit="metre">0.87</depth></dimensions>.
                              The front corner akroteria 
                              are carved with a sleeping Eros at right, a reclining female at left; the front of the roof has six sets of pan- and cover tiles, 
                              two of which end in the corner akroteria, the others in lions’ heads at the edge of the roof; 
                              both ends have a recessed tympanon with a winged Gorgoneion head. The sarcophagus survives, uninscribed.</p> </support>
